---

## The one rule
Claude drafts and interrogates; humans decide and own. Every gate below exists to enforce it:
a machine reports, a named human signs.

## The build loop (every story runs this)
**Intent → Delegate → Discern → merged & deployed to dev.**
- **Intent** — a human writes a short, testable spec (`specs/NNNN-name.md`). No spec, no build.
- **Delegate** — you (the agent) plan and build inside the spec's stated bounds. The plan is
  approved before code on MEDIUM/HIGH work.
- **Discern** — automated gates plus a **non-author** human check it before it is trusted.

## Definition of Ready (a story before anyone builds it)
- Acceptance criteria pass the **vague-line test**: *could two people build different things
  from this line?* If yes, it's a wish, not a check — rewrite it.
- Scope in / out stated. The silent decisions answered (no open decision-list item for this story).
- A **risk tier** assigned. The harness context named.

## Definition of Checked (a change before it merges)
Proven against its spec by something other than its author. Written is cheap; **checked is the bar.**
The climb is set by risk tier — see the checking ladder below.

---

## Risk taxonomy (the tier sets the gates)
Assigned by the {{POD_LEAD_ROLE}} at intent triage, recorded in the spec, and lived here so
agents see it too. **Challenges escalate up, never down, without discussion.**

| Tier | Lands here | Triggers |
|---|---|---|
| **HIGH** | Auth / identity, payments, PII / client data, schema migrations, public API contract changes, IaC / pipeline changes, **prompt / model / tool-definition changes**, anything hard to undo | Tight agent permissions · full checking ladder · security-reviewer pass · **named human sign-off recorded in the PR** |
| **MEDIUM** | New business logic, external integrations, changes to shared internal services | Standard permissions · grader + non-author human Checker |
| **LOW** | UI within existing patterns, copy, internal tooling, additive CRUD on established rails | Lighter review; grader + mechanical gates still run |

## The checking ladder (you don't run every change up all five rungs)
| Rung | Check | Catches |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Done-rule in this file | Sets the bar; persuasion only |
| 2 | Agent re-checks each turn | The agent's own mechanical slips |
| 3 | Blocking **Stop hook** | "Done" on red tests / broken build |
| 4 | Separate **grader** | The hole the author was blind to — check-by-check vs the spec |
| 5 | **Human / security gate** | Judgment calls no machine should own |

LOW stops after the grader's advisory + a light human look. MEDIUM = grader + Checker.
HIGH = all five rungs, including security-reviewer and a named human sign-off.

